2. **What are the key principles of Agile?**
   - Customer satisfaction through early and continuous delivery.(Review)
   - Welcome changing requirements, even late in development.(Frequent Change Requests)
   - Deliver working software frequently.(Iterative Working Software)
   - Business and developers must work together daily.(Daily Standups)
   - Build projects around motivated individuals.(Team collaboration)
   - Face-to-face conversation is the best form of communication.(Daily Standups)
   - Working software is the primary measure of progress.(Iterative Working Software)
   - Sustainable development is promoted.(Retrospective)
   - Continuous attention to technical excellence and good design.(Retrospective)
   - Simplicity is essential.
   - Self-organizing teams are encouraged.
   - Reflect on how to become more effective regularly.(Retrospective)